@node inst "Instructions"

You should already know how to browse Amiga Guide-documents.

First click "Start here" to reach the index table of World Cups.

There you see the tournament year, host and medalists of that
tournament.

Clicking the year (example @{"1930" link 1930}) You'll see the
playing system,scores,groups,goalscorers of that tournament
and all the teams.
When you click a team (example @{"Argentina" link arg30}) then
you'll get a namelist of that team and the goals they've scored.
Clicking the match (example @{"FRA-MEX 4-1" link FM30}) will
reveal the scorers of that game.

Clicking the host (example @{"Uruguay" link host30}) You'll get
some statistics of that tournament (goals scored, spectators etc.)

Clicking the medalists you simply get the namelist of that team
plus the goals they've scored.

@endnode
@node history "History"

I started this project because I wasn't able to get my hands on any
soccer-related cd-roms available for Amiga.
On a different view, I have read lots and lots of World Cup books
and practically every book has more or less wrong statistics.

So my aim is to make this guide a 100 % perfect statistic package.
It's hard and probably impossible to make such a thing but the
show still goes on.

